  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant HR Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Handle monthly payroll processing and all statutory submissions.</p></li><li><p>Manage the end-to-end recruitment process, including screening CVs, conducting initial interviews, and coordinating with hiring managers to ensure a smooth selection process.</p></li><li><p>Manage onboarding and offboarding, including contracts, work pass matters, orientation, and exit procedures.</p></li><li><p>Maintain employee records and HR documents.</p></li><li><p>Assist in employee relations matters including grievances, disciplinary actions, investigations, and dispute resolution; Support employee engagement initiatives and action plans.</p></li><li><p>Assist in HR operations, performance appraisals, and any ad-hoc HR tasks.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum 5 years of HR experiences.</p></li><li><p>Familiar with Singapore Employment Act and Employment of Foreign Manpower Act.</p></li><li><p>Resourceful, detail-oriented, and independent, with the confidence to seek guidance when needed.</p></li><li><p>Strong communicator who enjoys working with people at all levels.</p></li><li><p>Excited to grow your career in HR and step up into a senior role in the future.</p></li><li><p>Looking for suitable applicant who is immediate available.</p></li></ul>",
